LinkedIn has introduced Ask for a Referral to make it easier for jobseekers to apply for a job at a new company where they know someone. Referrals are one of the best ways to get your foot in the door at a new company, with 50% of recruiters saying referrals are the leading source of quality hires, it said. Jobseekers who have received a referral from a person in a company are four-times more likely to hear back from a recruiter at that company. LinkedInâ€™s Ask for a Referral lets users: